    <obo:IAO_0000115>Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stress acting at the endoplasmic reticulum. ER stress usually results from the accumulation of unfolded or misfolded proteins in the ER lumen.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <rdfs:label>response to endoplasmic reticulum stress</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
