    <owl:annotatedTarget>The series of molecular signals in which an intracellular signal is conveyed to trigger the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway is induced in response to nitrosative stress; a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of nitric oxide (NO) or the highly reactive oxidant peroxynitrite, which is produced following interaction of NO with superoxide anions.</owl:annotatedTarget>
    <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>GOC:PARL</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>GOC:bf</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
