  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0097190">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0007165"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="N7ce30de1925d485693e520f0fb030b13"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="N991d6cd8e7c746aaae0730bbd02186f5"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="Na1717125830c492684a625c501550660"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The series of molecular signals which triggers the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway starts with reception of a signal, and ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <obo:RO_0002161 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_4896"/>
    <oboInOwl:created_by>pr</oboInOwl:created_by>
    <oboInOwl:creation_date>2011-11-23T09:30:23Z</oboInOwl:creation_date>
    <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>GO:0008624</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
    <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>Reactome:R-HSA-193681</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>Reactome:R-HSA-204998</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>Reactome:R-HSA-75157</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
    <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>apoptotic signalling pathway</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
    <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>induction of apoptosis by extracellular signals</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
    <oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>biological_process</oboInOwl:hasOBONamespace>
    <oboInOwl:id>GO:0097190</oboInOwl:id>
    <rdfs:comment>This term can be used to annotate gene products involved in apoptotic events happening downstream of the cross-talk point between the extrinsic and intrinsic apoptotic pathways. The cross-talk starts when caspase-8 cleaves Bid and truncated Bid interacts with mitochondria. From this point on it is not possible to distinguish between extrinsic and intrinsic pathways.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>apoptotic signaling pathway</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N90be77ca57594c3389279c8e650decb4">
