  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0033554">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <rdfs:label>cellular response to stress</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
