  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0043029">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <obo:IAO_0000115>The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of T cells such that the total number of T cells within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.</obo:IAO_0000115>
    <rdfs:comment>Note that this term represents the return of T cell levels to stable numbers following an immune response as well as the proliferation and elimination of T cells required to maintain stable numbers in the absence of an outside stimulus.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>T cell homeostasis</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
